dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Formby, drift, sheet 83
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 83 drift. In upper left corner: Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 53.616700. South Decimal Degree 53.4500. East Decimal Degree -2.9333. West Decimal Degree -3.3500. In the upper left corner: Ordnance Survey of England (Third Edition). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological by C. E. De Rance published in 1869, revised 1873. Resurveyed in 1927, 1930, and 1937, by F. W. Cope, et al.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1942.
